The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 More chances for challenged

 New Delhi, May 9 (PTI): Physically-challenged candidates belonging to the general category will get seven chances to appear for the civil services examinations.

 Currently, they can make four attempts like other general category candidates.

 Recently, a policy decision has been taken that physically-handicapped candidates belonging to the general category will get seven attempts. This is being implemented with prospective effect, Union minister for personnel Suresh Pachauri told the Lok Sabha today. Now, such OBC candidates can make seven attempts, while SC/ST aspirants can make unlimited attempts.




